    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nAn if/elif/else chain whose conditions use the is identity operator is miscompiled in Cython 3.3.0a1 — the else clause is emitted as a bare unconditional C block. When the matched branch falls through (noreturn/raise/break), control also drops into the else, so both branches run. == chains are unaffected.\n\nBroken codegen:\n```\n__pyx_t_1 = (__pyx_v_x == Py_None);\nif (__pyx_t_1) { ... print(\"matched None\") ... }\n/*else*/ { ... print(\"else branch\") ... }   // no `else`, no goto: ALWAYS runs\n```\n\nMasked by return/raise.\nAffects `def` and `cdef`.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\ndef f(x):\n    if x is None:\n        print(\"matched None\")\n    else:\n        print(\"else branch\")\n\nf(None)\n```\nprints both _matched None_ and _else branch_!\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nOnly one branch is taken!\n\n### OS\n\nLinux Fedora 44\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14.6\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.3.0a1\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
