        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The other thing to add here is that `Nodes.py` isn't in the standard compilation that we do. It's only set if you do `CYTHON_COMPILE_ALL=true` (which wasn't one of the combinations I tested yesterday). It is a combination that we test on the CI though (probably not with LTO) and I've just given it a go locally so I'm inclined to believe that it's something with your GCC and build flags rather than a general problem.\n\nI suspect LTO doesn't add a lot for building Cython itself (because one `.o` file goes to `.so` file so there shouldn't be any optimizations that it can't do without LTO). It may be worthwhile when building stuff does do useful linking here.",
