            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> this is a GCC LTO bug\n\nThanks for reporting back. These issues are _really_ annoying and time consuming when they happen. Luckily, it's rare that they occur – which is why it's even more annoying because it's the last place where I'd look.\n\nAlso, good to know that distributors have considered `--cython-compile-all` as a packaging option. For us, it's more of a \"use it if you really, really want\" kind of setting, but it can make good sense for packages that are built-once-installed-often-but-run-millions-of-times, thus favouring even unimpressive speed advantages over size. And it's probably also worth the slightly reduced build times of Cython based packages in a distribution like Fedora that quickly adds up over the days. The option is basically covered in our CI and benchmark runs, though, probably sufficiently to have us notified if things go really wrong (… in other ways than a specific C compiler hickup).",
